    "headline": "Starbucks to lay off 300 US corporate workers and close regional offices",
    "summary": "Starbucks said Friday it’s laying off 300 corporate employees and closing some U.S. offices as part of its ongoing turnaround.  The cuts will impact employees in support functions like marketing, human resources and supply chain management.  No international employees are affected for now, but Starbucks said it is also reviewing its corporate structure outside the U.S.",
